HEADWORD: lipid-lowering
<hw>lipid-lowering</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Serving to
reduce the concentration of lipid, such as cholesterol, in the blood; --
of medications, such as <er>Mevinolin</er>, that are used especially to
reduce blood cholesterol, as a preventive measure against heart
disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lipidosis</ent>⟦br⟧
